mastery.question_text:
Sam says the arrow points to $-2$. Explain why this is wrong and give the correct value.
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw[{Stealth}-{Stealth}] (-3.4,0)--(3.4,0);
\foreach \v in {-10,-8,...,10} {\draw (0.3*\v,0.12)--(0.3*\v,-0.12);}
\foreach \v in {-10,0,10} {\node[below] at (0.3*\v,-0.16) {$\v$};}
\draw[-{Stealth}] (-1.2,0.62)--(-1.2,0.14);
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

Mark $-6$ on the number line. Read the scale first.
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw[{Stealth}-{Stealth}] (-3.4,0)--(3.4,0);
\foreach \v in {-10,-8,...,10} {\draw (0.3*\v,0.12)--(0.3*\v,-0.12);}
\foreach \v in {-10,0,10} {\node[below] at (0.3*\v,-0.16) {$\v$};}
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

mastery.solution_text:
$-10$ to $0$ is $5$ intervals, so each interval is $2$.
$-6$ is $3$ intervals left of $0$.
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw[{Stealth}-{Stealth}] (-3.4,0)--(3.4,0);
\foreach \v in {-10,-8,...,10} {\draw (0.3*\v,0.12)--(0.3*\v,-0.12);}
\foreach \v in {-10,0,10} {\node[below] at (0.3*\v,-0.16) {$\v$};}
\fill (-1.8,0) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above] at (-1.8,0.2) {$-6$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

